@startuml Account Management Use Case Diagram

left to right direction

actor "Regular User" as User
actor "Admin" as Admin
actor "Super Admin" as SuperAdmin
actor "Email System" as EmailSystem

rectangle "Account Management System" {
    usecase "Register Account" as UC1
    usecase "Verify Email" as UC2
    usecase "Login" as UC3
    usecase "Refresh Token" as UC4
    usecase "Create Admin Account" as UC5
    usecase "Delete Admin Account" as UC6
    usecase "View All Admins" as UC7
}

User --> UC1 : requests registration
User --> UC2 : verifies email
User --> UC3 : logs in
User --> UC4 : refreshes token

SuperAdmin --> UC5 : creates admin accounts
SuperAdmin --> UC6 : deletes admin accounts
SuperAdmin --> UC7 : views admin list

UC1 --> EmailSystem : sends verification code
UC2 --> EmailSystem : receives verification code

note right of UC1
    User provides: name, email, password
    System sends 6-digit verification code
end note

note right of UC2
    User enters verification code
    Account becomes verified and active
end note

note right of UC3
    User provides email and password
    System returns access and refresh tokens
end note

note right of UC4
    User provides refresh token
    System returns new access and refresh tokens
end note

note right of UC5
    Super Admin creates new Admin account
    Admin is automatically verified
end note

note right of UC6
    Super Admin deletes existing Admin account
end note

note right of UC7
    Super Admin views list of all Admin accounts
end note

@enduml
